H0.text: Ticks feeding on a dog is a parasitic symbiotic relationship.

H1.text: Bees transporting pollen from flowers is a symbiotic relationship considered parasitic.

H2.text: Pilotfish swimming under sharks is a parasitic symbiotic relationship.

H3.text: Birds eating the insects from the back of a hippopotamus is considered a parasitic symbiotic relationship.

A4.text: Ticks are obligate hematophages, and require blood to survive and move from one stage of life to another.

A5.text: Because of their hematophagous (blood-ingesting) diets, ticks act as vectors of many serious diseases that affect humans and other animals.
